WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:03.920
These are the best preserved medieval&nbsp;
walled cities in Europe. The last one's&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:03.920 --> 00:00:09.680
too good to be true. Carcassonne, France.&nbsp;
Double concentric walls, over 50 towers,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:09.680 --> 00:00:14.080
a church, a castle. It looks straight out&nbsp;
of a fairy tale, but much of what you see&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:14.080 --> 00:00:20.400
today was restored in the 19th century. York,&nbsp;
England. 4 km of walls, Roman foundations,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:20.400 --> 00:00:25.920
medieval gates. Walk the ramparts toward York&nbsp;
Minster. Arguably the best view in the city.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:25.920 --> 00:00:32.000
Avignon, France built by popes in the 14th&nbsp;
century. 4 km of walls encircle the entire&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:38.320
city. Add the massive palace of the popes and&nbsp;
it feels frozen in time. But then there's Avila,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:38.320 --> 00:00:46.000
Spain. 2 and a half km of perfectly intact granite&nbsp;
walls. 86 identical towers, 10 monumental gates.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:52.720
Even the cathedral is half church, half fortress.&nbsp;
12 m high, almost untouched. Easily one of the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:52.720 --> 00:00:56.720
most dramatic medieval cities in Europe.&nbsp;
